{
  "doc_id": "17765",
  "text": "Romidepsin (FK228) is a class I HDAC inhibitor [CITATION_1] and was the second FDA-approved HDAC inhibitor for the treatment of refractory CTCL and PTCL [CITATION_2] . It induces apoptosis and inhibits proliferation and metastasis of GBM cells [CITATION_3] . Romidepsin was studied in a phase I/ II trial on patients with recurrent high-grade gliomas, but at the standard dose and schedule, it was ineffective for patients with recurrent GBM (NCT00085540) [CITATION_4] .",
